{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"af9a7dae-6966-4b7b-ab2c-a100a216995b","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theory:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results and display your reason message in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fa511f5b-a469-4933-abed-310ddfaf293b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a general knowledge question that I can answer directly without needing to look anything up.","outputTokens":212,"requestId":"E3E4:139515:552603:624DC5:6A052397"},"id":"4b90a597-6f4e-413d-96ed-3c693576f39f","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:21:33.468Z","parentId":"e4d48d74-3de7-4364-91b6-9b01ef2a0d54"}
